00:45:28,931 --> 00:45:32,193
sudden, later in Act Two, when we're exploring one of those

821
00:45:32,193 --> 00:45:33,074
Act Two areas,

822
00:45:33,748 --> 00:45:37,730
at the very end of an area, he would pop up out of nowhere,

823
00:45:37,730 --> 00:45:39,511
suddenly corrupted, suddenly dangerous,

824
00:45:39,511 --> 00:45:41,012
and we have to fight him.

825
00:45:41,012 --> 00:45:44,854
And it was too difficult for the player to remember,

826
00:45:44,854 --> 00:45:47,995
you know, the last time they saw Kolok,

827
00:45:47,995 --> 00:45:49,716
to understand why he might've been corrupted,

828
00:45:49,716 --> 00:45:52,318
did it come from the water and all this kind of stuff.

829
00:45:52,318 --> 00:45:54,639
Basically, ultimately, what we wanted

830
00:45:54,639 --> 00:45:57,801
was going to require a lot more work.

831
00:45:57,801 --> 00:46:01,883
It was gonna require a lot more story beats, sort of.

832
00:46:02,442 --> 00:46:05,903
intertwined throughout this experience and a little bit more justification.

833
00:46:05,903 --> 00:46:12,184
So on the front of justification, rather than just saying that it was just this sort of ambiguous

834
00:46:12,184 --> 00:46:17,306
corruption that was happening to him because of the water, we decided to create a parasite,

835
00:46:17,306 --> 00:46:22,947
pretty much, called the foul presence or the stink spirit, that basically was the thing that was

836
00:46:22,947 --> 00:46:27,708
clogging up the mill. And this served, you know, it solved a number of problems, pretty much,

837
00:46:27,708 --> 00:46:29,829
because it added sort of a face to this corruption.

838
00:46:30,374 --> 00:46:34,015
It made the escape sequence a lot more interesting.

